The first SSDs used volatile [DRAM](/Dynamic_random-access_memory) for storage, but since 2009 most SSDs utilize non‑volatile [NAND flash](/NAND_flash) memory, which retains data even when powered off. &#91;52&#93; &#91;3&#93; Flash memory SSDs store data in [metal–oxide–semiconductor](/MOSFET) (MOS) integrated circuit chips, using non‑volatile [floating‑gate](/Floating-gate_MOSFET) memory cells. &#91;53&#93;

